social_posts.post_text: When you accidentally rent the most magical Airbnb ever ❄️ I’m officially in the holiday spirit. Happy December 1st everyone.

Pass the parcel ✨ one of my favorite Christmas traditions. Use newspaper instead of plastic! That’s what we will be doing this year. We did this for the first time last year at our party and it was so fun.

How to play:
- you pass the parcel around in a circle
- the person next to the parcel is rolling dice and as soon as they get doubles you have to pass it on
- we make everyone wear oven mitts so it takes longer to unwrap
- whatever you get unwrapped on your turn you get to keep!

#passtheparcel #christmasparty #partygames #partyinspiration

This year we are LIVING WITH LESS. Between buying our home and doing our remodel we haven’t done a big declutter. We are overwhelmed with the amount of STUFF.

I embarked on this office remodel in Feb of 2022 and now in April of 2023 we can finally say the project is complete. This room challenged me. Balancing doing DIY in a space that wasn’t my own along with keeping everything at home going tested me. I was in two separate car accidents during this project. My sweet grandma Irene (who inspired and encouraged me to start this account) passed. Sometimes life just doesn’t take into account what your plans are. I did projects and DIYSs I have never done before. There is nothing that makes me feel more alive than working with my own two hands and seeing something come to life. That fact that I get to do this and share with all of you is truly a gift.

I want to thank YOU. The amount of excitement and celebration I felt with each one of your comments and DMs really encouraged me and pushed me forward. I am so grateful that you choose to spend some of your time with me. This POP Family is such a gift.

I just replaced all of my flooring in my upstairs and here is how I did it: 

🔨 Step 1: Prepare your subfloor, ensuring a smooth and stable foundation for your laminate flooring installation. Removed all carpet, tack strips, nails, staples, etc. You will also need to remove your baseboards. 

📐 Step 2: Measure and plan for your room. Use an online calculator to determine the amount of laminate flooring needed, and plan the layout for a seamless result.

⚙️ Step 3: Gathering the Tools and Materials - you will need flooring, a flooring installation kit, a way to cut your boards, knee pads, and a tape measure.

📝 Step 4: You will need to acclimate your flooring which means you need to have it delivered at least 2 weeks before install.

🏗️ Step 5: Installing the Underlayment - there are many different kinds and it depends on what type of subfloor you are installing on. 

🔩 Step 6: Laying the Laminate Flooring - this will vary from product to product so make sure you watch a video on YT with your exact brand and model

🔨 Step 7: Cutting and Fitting Around Obstacles - to do this we used a Dremel multi tool. 

🧹 Step 8: Finishing Touches - reinstall your baseboards 

🎉 Step 9: Enjoy Your Beautiful New Floor!
Once you’ve completed the installation, it’s time to revel in the satisfaction of your stunning new laminate floor. Sit back, relax, and enjoy your transformed space!

🚨CONFESSION 🚨: Fall decor DOES NOT DO IT FOR ME OKAY? I said it. Red and orange are not my jam so every year I struggle with it unless I can make it NEUTRAL. Here I am trying to embrace fall colors on my own terms… muted style. How did I do??? Would you try it?

🍂 DOLLAR STORE DIY fall edition 🍂 

Supplies: 
3 leaf trays (dollar tree)
9 round beads 
Hot glue
Paint
Baking soda 

Glue three beads to the bottom of each leaf tray and allow them to dry. Mix baking soda, and paint together in a ratio of one to one and paint your leaf tray top and bottom. You will need to do 2 to 3 coats, depending on the texture you want. Let dry. Voila!
